	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=215998><span id= >vikingprin</span></a><br><span id=notbold>4 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>OK, so I was told initially that you need a good strong group to kill these sirens... Well after several rounds of getting my &quot;good strong group&quot; wiped out, they all left except my lvl 52 bard (luv ya Lutrum!) and we realized it was easier for just the two of us. And 3 shawl fails later we have a pretty good system worked out. Heres what we do:<br><br>I sit on the beach (I found that hiding behind a big rock seems to help this cleric avoid aggro... dont ask me why, but i feel safer anyways) and he goes over the water around the bulthars to tag the sirens.&nbsp;&nbsp;With our combined MRs, he resists around 95pct of their spells. By the time they get back to the beach they have usually run oom from chain casting and they are an easy kill. Also, when he does get charmed he runs up the hill and attacks the druids up top hunting wyverns(stupid soloable classes deserve a little extra aggro.......=P) which leaves me alive and safe to rezz if necessary. And if you have trouble finding a bard to help you out, we have picked up about one conch shell horn for every 2 or 3 hairs, so they will most likely get a nice little instrument by the time you are done. Hope this helps someone :)<br><br>Namene Pineaway, 51 cleric<br><br>PS a bard MAY be able to solo them for the other quest, but their nukes seem to  land more often than other spells, especially when we get two, so he often needs a heal or two mid fight... go together, share the love <br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Mar 20 06:32:26 2003</em></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
