	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=85336><span id= >bretappleby</span></a><br><span id=notbold>33 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.30]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I have been soloing these (as a bard) from level 53 but you may be able to earlier.&nbsp;&nbsp;I have tried fighting underwater but I found the lack in manoeuvrability and the sharks adding a liability.  I have been pulling to the Sirens Grotto zone, fairly easy to single-pull just by slowly going down the tunnel and waiting for proximity agro.  The agro from a long way and the first you will know is when spells hit you(or hopefully you resist them).<br><br>I always (unless I was mezzing them) played Psalm of Mystic shielding (Magic Resist) and I did work on getting my MR up with equipment to about 90 before singing.  Previously when I tried it was the nukes that hurt.  Once the agro’d me I slowly backed up to land until they left the water - there I mezzed them (healed if necessary) and de-buffed to get rid of runes and damage shields.  From there I straight meeleed (fear kiting took too long) and mez healed if necessary.  Most times I didn't need to mez heal as I could melee the dark blues 50% of the time in one go.<br><br>Sometimes  2 came at once - 3 options 1.  Charm one to kill the other then zone 2. Charm one to kill other then melee ex-pet 3.  Zone and try again.  All 3 worked for me.<br><br>4 Deaths before trying this tactic, none since, have failed on one combine, and now I'm ready for the next one, wish me luck.<br></p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
